PN,44204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1778170272
OL,3,CTroubles legacy law did not diminish
OL,4,Cvictims' rights, Supreme Court rules
OL,6,FDespite efforts to change the law, the
OL,7,FNorthern Ireland Office still took the
OL,8,Fcase to the Supreme Court over the
OL,9,Fapplication of the Windsor Framework,
OL,10,Ftelling a hearing last October that
OL,11,Fthe issue was "constitutionally
OL,12,Fprofound".
OL,14,FFour Troubles victims ` Martina
OL,15,FDillon, John McEvoy, Brigid Hughes and
OL,16,FLynda McManus ` opposed the challenge,
OL,17,Fwith their lawyers telling the UK's
OL,18,Fhighest court that NICA was "plainly
OL,19,Fcorrect".
OL,26,@sD@OOUtD@IO]zD@]OU{D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
